In this article, President Trump discusses various topics during a press conference in Hanoi, Vietnam. He mentions the ongoing conflict between Pakistan and India and expresses hope for a resolution. He also discusses the situation in Venezuela and the efforts to send supplies to the country. The president then talks about his meeting with North Korean leader Kim Jong Un, stating that they had a productive time but decided not to sign any agreements at this point. He emphasizes the importance of sanctions and the need for North Korea to denuclearize. Trump also addresses the issue of Otto Warmbier's death and his discussions with Kim on the matter. He concludes by mentioning his upcoming meeting with Chinese President Xi Jinping and the potential for a peace deal between Israel and Palestine.